# Prefer events over timers

Do not use `QTimer`, `singleShot(0)`, or arbitrary delays when the codebase already has a clear logical point to run the work.

## Use instead

- **Observer / callback completion** — e.g. after `Perform(&IObserver::On…)` returns, synchronous observers have run.
- **Existing state transitions** — load finished, model updated, cache hit, executor task callback.
- **Explicit API** — `OnXxxDone()`, `finished` signal, `IExecutor` completion handler.

## Timers are OK when

- Debouncing rapid user input (search, resize coalescing).
- Polling or periodic refresh with no event source.
- Delay is a real product requirement (auto-hide, idle timeout).
- No hook exists yet and adding one would be disproportionate — document why.

## Anti-patterns

- `start(0)` / `singleShot(0)` only to “run after” code that already has a completion path.
- Timer to order two steps that share a parent function or observer chain.
